I absolutely love the song and the video. I've been a fan of The Strokes since the beginning. I'm also a 1970s fan, so I like the fact that the video is supposed to be 1972.

I also have to say that the guys look really good here. I thought they were starting to look rough (we all know how it is with rockers) but I could have been wrong. Or maybe they've gotten into using moisturizer and going to spa treatments.

snippet.textDisplay: I feel like The Strokes posted this to prove a point. Their song At The Door is completely original song with amazing original artwork for the video, yet this is the song that is trending and popular among most people, which is ironic because the video refers to the fact that people will take knock-off or ripped off versions of things and they took melodies from two iconic songs. I just really feel like they are having a laugh about it.
